<DocsLayout title="Home">
  <h1>Soundweave</h1>
  <p class="docs-subtitle">
    Adaptive soundtrack authoring for AI-driven RPG worlds
  </p>

  <p>
    Soundweave is a toolkit for designing, previewing, and exporting structured
    soundtrack packs. Instead of hand-scripting music transitions, you define
    <strong>assets</strong>, <strong>stems</strong>, <strong>scenes</strong>,
    <strong>trigger bindings</strong>, and <strong>transitions</strong> — then
    let the runtime decide what plays and when.
  </p>

  <h2>What you get</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Studio</strong> — a browser-based editor for authoring packs with
      live preview and export
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Schema</strong> — canonical types and validators for all
      soundtrack data
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Runtime Pack</strong> — export and import runtime-ready JSON
      soundtrack packs
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Review</strong> — automated summaries, audits, and health checks
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Audio Engine</strong> — scene evaluation, binding resolution, and
      transition modeling
    </li>
  </ul>

